# LLM Watchdog Daemon
# Monitors sonia's macbook llama-server health

NAME llm-watchdog

INPUT llm_host DEFAULT "100.75.170.108"
INPUT llm_port DEFAULT "8080"
INPUT broker_url DEFAULT "http://100.109.211.128:7899"

GOAL watch_llm """Check the LLM server on sonia's macbook and report status.

Steps:
1. curl http://$llm_host:$llm_port/health — check if server responds
2. curl http://$llm_host:$llm_port/slots — check slot utilization
3. curl http://$llm_host:$llm_port/metrics — check token throughput and error rates

Report:
- Server status (up/down)
- Active slots vs total
- Token throughput (prompt t/s, generation t/s)
- Any anomalies (high memory, stuck slots, zero throughput with active requests)

If the server is DOWN:
- Try to reach the host via ssh sonia@$llm_host 'echo ok'
- If host is reachable but server is down, report that llama-server needs restart
- Publish alert via: curl -X POST $broker_url/send-message with a message to all active peers

Keep output concise. One paragraph summary."""

RUN main USING watch_llm
